      "text": "Here are the summaries and key exports for each file:\n\n---\n\n## 1. `app/(main)/page.tsx`\n\n**Summary:**  \nThis is the main landing page (home page) of the LlamaCoder application. It presents a prompt input form where users can describe an app idea, select an AI model and quality level (low/high), and optionally upload a screenshot. On submission, it calls the API to create a chat session and redirects the user to the chat page. It also displays suggested prompts, a powered-by banner, and a footer with social links.\n\n**Key exports / functions / APIs:**\n- **`Home` (default export)** — The main page component. Manages state for `prompt`, `model`, `quality`, `screenshotUrl`, and submission flow.\n- **`Footer`** — Memoized component rendering a footer with \"Built with Llama and Together AI\" text and social links (X/Twitter, GitHub).\n- **`LoadingMessage`** — A sub-component shown during submission with contextual messages (e.g., \"Creating your app...\", \"Analyzing your screenshot...\", or high-quality notice).\n- **Exported constants** — `runtime = \"edge\"` and `maxDuration = 60` (Next.js edge runtime configuration).\n- **API calls:** `POST /api/create-chat` (creates a new chat session) and `POST /api/get-next-completion-stream-promise` (initiates the streaming response).\n\n---\n\n## 2. `components/header.tsx`\n\n**Summary:**  \nA simple, memoized header component that displays the LlamaCoder logo and Together AI branding as a clickable link back to the home page. On the right side, it shows a GitHub link button with a star count (\"6k stars\"), linking to the upstream `nutlope/llamacoder` repository.\n\n**Key exports / functions / APIs:**\n- **`Header` (default export, wrapped in `memo`)** — The header component. Uses `next/image` for logos and `next/link` for internal navigation.\n\n---\n\n## 3. `components/code-runner.tsx`\n\n**Summary:**  \nA thin wrapper component that delegates rendering to a child component (`CodeRunnerReact` from `./code-runner-react`). Its primary responsibility is normalizing the input: if a `code` string is provided without a `files` array, it wraps it into a single-file structure with path `\"App.tsx\"`. This ensures the downstream `CodeRunnerReact` always receives a consistent `files` array format.\n\n**Key exports / functions / APIs:**\n- **`CodeRunner` (default export)** — Accepts `language?`, `code?`, `files?` (array of `{ path: string; content: string }`), and `onRequestFix?` (callback to request a code fix with an error message). Renders `<CodeRunnerReact>` with the normalized files array.\n- **`onRequestFix`** — An optional callback prop of type `(e: string) => void`, allowing parent components to request fixes when the code runner encounters an error.",
